<br>
Darkness contains 4 core values.<br>
<br>
Hate, Fear, War/Combat, and Death<br>
<br>
To be apart of darkness, you have to be apart of one of these 4 values, by your religion.<br>
<br>
Darkness is based almost soely on religion. The easiest way to see if you are dark or not is to see what religion you follow.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">If you follow these Gods:</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
Innoruuk ~ The God of Hate<br>
Cazic Thule ~ The God of Fear<br>
Bertoxxullos ~ The God of Death<br>
<br>
You are dark.<br>
<br>
Their are also accepted Demigods that many follow in conjunction with the above three.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now, when we get to the more wide spread religions, we look to see if you truly are dark or not. Some of the Gods do enjoy watching their followers fight, so they have sprinkled their followers across both darkness and the light, and they have done this to watch their followers fight. They seperated them by race, to be clear.<br>
<br>
The Gods in Question are<br>
<br>
Rallos Zek ~ The God of War<br>
Soluseck Ro ~ The Burning Prince<br>
Fizzlethorpe Bristlebane ~ Only because some of his more Malious side.<br>
<br>
Also, the Demigods have to share this fate, because it is harder to identify their followers.. namely..<br>
<br>
Saryrn<br>
Terris Thule<br>
Lanys T'Vyl<br>
Lord Platium (Kyri's god of Money &amp; Greed)<br>
Agnostic (No god at all)<br>
<br>
The thing about these gods is that this is the only time where your RACE comes into question. The accepted races that follow these gods are as follows..<br>
<br>
Darkelf (Tier'dal)<br>
Humans<br>
Ogres (As the Children of Rallos Zek, they are dark)<br>
Trolls<br>
Erudites<br>
Gnomes<br>
Half elves<br>
<br>
If you follow the gods above and you are one of the races above, you are dark.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Agnostics are on a CASE BY CASE</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
How to lose your right to be dark, ~ GUILDS ~<br>
<br>
People underestimate the power of a guild. Joining a guild means that you put yourself and tolerate people that you will fight along side, befriend, and generally trust and defend.<br>
The easisest way to lose your darkness is to belong to a guild with lightbringers in it. WHO is a Lightbringer?<br>
<br>
Well, the easy thing to say is that if they are not on this list, then they are a lightbringer.<br>
<br>
The Lightbringer races are as follows...<br>
<br>
Woodelf, Highelf, Dwarf, Halfling, Vah Shir, Barbarian, Froglok<br>
<br>
And the lightbringer classes are as follows...<br>
<br>
Ranger, Druid, Paladin, <br>
<br>
The Lightbringer Gods..<br>
<br>
Tunare, Mithanel Marr and his Sister, Karana, Brell Serillis, Prexus, Quellos, Veeshan, The Tribunal, Rodcet Nife<br>
<br>
If you are in a guild with any of these.. then you are in a Lightbringer guild.<br>
<br>
A person in a lightbringer guild is sligtly better then a lightbringer.<br>
<br>
Depending on who you are, you may live. You may die. Maybe you will be converted to see the true darkness that you should be fighting along side..<br>
<br>
Or maybe you will be dead for your countless assistance to those of the light. That choice belongs to us.<br>
<br>
The above has been cleared by the Citizens of the Necropolis as the generic standards of Darkness. The below has not.<br>
<br>
Dark Orginizations within Norrath: (NPCs)<br>
Notice that some factions you will NOT be able to please. Their tolerance is so low that they will strike at ANYONE.<br>
<br>
Some of them even fight one another. Some are stuck believing that since they are dark, they must battle one another.. or some just wish to destroy everyone at once.<br>
<br>
No one ever said that was a bad thing. Here they are as follows, in no order at all.<br>
<br>
As for what to do with them.. that is at your own discression<br>
<br>
