<br>
Turning back to the rest of the room, she scans the faces of those gathered. &quot;Our most honorable Swifttail visitor's right. There's a bit of confusion as to this whole darkness, light, good, evil thing, yes? Especially since you can &quot;follow&quot; one of the 'gods' but not truly act in their service, yet still be 'dark.' This 'darkness' is like... an exclusive club for the Teir'Dal and their slaves -- er, 'friends.'&quot;<br>
<br>
She narrows her eyes slightly, and a soft dissonant chord rises in the background, barely loud enough to hear, but more than loud enough to cast an air of apprehension over the room. &quot;Make <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>no</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> mistake -- everyone is evil, 'dark' or not. Evil is your birthright. When your lover betrays you, when your 'god' commands you to kill in his name, when you slaughter for your own end -- you channel that evil into the world. <br>
<br>
&quot;But evil actions are just that. You're not more evil because you follow some 'god' or happen to have been born the right race. No. You're evil because you choose to be honest about what you are.<br>
<br>
&quot;Being evil and being 'dark' aren't the same thing. Nor are good and being a 'lightbringer' the same thing. This other layer of 'dark' and 'light' splits the forces of evil, makes them weak.&quot;<br>
<br>
She smiles and winks at Shintou. &quot;Though not that I really think any Druid, Feir'Dal, or Koada'Dal -- bastard supporters of the balance that they are -- could ever come to terms with the evil within themselves.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=seuinye>Seuinye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/29/03 3:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No longer evil, just truly DARK.</span><hr size=1> *grins, and orders the Pera'dal and Vah Shir another round of drinks, sitting back with wicked laughter in her eyes* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=koscha>Koscha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/29/03 3:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lionking.org/~black/art/koscha/koscha.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No longer evil, just truly DARK.</span><hr size=1> Koscha waits until Elluden is finished before murmuring to her in a quiet voice.  &quot;I thank you for the compliment, but I am not of the Empire.&quot;<br>
<br>
It is a small thing, perhaps, but apparantly quite important to her.<br>
